13. MVP SCOPE
The MVP is designed to deliver the fastest, safest, most emotionally satisfying inbox cleanup experience, without unnecessary complexity.

The MVP must:

Deliver the core swipe experience

Support real email cleanup

Provide basic AI suggestions

Build trust and safety

Show clear emotional payoff

Avoid scope creep

Ship fast

This page defines:

What’s in

What’s out

What’s postponed

What’s essential

What’s optional

13.1 MVP Philosophy
1. Ship the dopamine loop first
The swipe experience is the product.

2. Safety > automation
Undo everywhere.
No auto‑actions.
No risky rules.

3. Metadata‑only AI
No content reading.
No hallucinations.
No generative behavior.

4. Emotion > features
The MVP must feel amazing.

5. Reduce engineering risk
Start with Gmail only.
Add others later.

13.2 What’s In (MVP)
These features are required for launch.

A. Core Swipe Experience
Included
Swipe left → delete

Swipe right → unsubscribe

Swipe up → block

Swipe down → keep

Long‑press → domain nuke (with confirmation)

Card stack (3‑card system)

Motion, tilt, color, icon previews

Haptics + sound

Undo system

Progress bar

Mini victory screen

Why?
This is the heart of the product.

B. Gmail Integration (Only Gmail for MVP)
Included
OAuth login

Fetch emails

Metadata normalization

Delete

Unsubscribe

Block (via Gmail filters)

Domain nuke (via Gmail filters)

Batch delete

Undo support

Why?
Gmail = 60–70% of target users.
Fastest path to launch.

C. Newsletter Detection Engine (MVP Version)
Included
List‑Unsubscribe detection

Gmail category detection

Sender domain reputation

Basic frequency detection

Heuristic scoring

Why?
Needed for swipe suggestions + sorting.

D. Internal AI Janitor (MVP Version)
Included
Basic sender reputation

Basic spam score

Simple action suggestions

No clustering

No insights

No automation suggestions

Why?
Just enough intelligence to feel smart.

E. Onboarding & Trust
Included
Welcome flow

Safety messaging

Permission explanation

Gmail connect

Tutorial swipe

First cleanup session

Why?
Trust is essential for inbox access.

F. Basic Insights (MVP Version)
Included
Emails cleared

Time saved

Top senders removed

Mini streak counter

Why?
Emotional payoff.

G. Database (MVP Version)
Included
Users

Email accounts

Emails

Senders

Domains

Actions

Undo tokens

Why?
Minimum needed for functionality.

13.3 What’s Out (Not in MVP)
These features are explicitly excluded from MVP.

A. Multi‑Provider Support
Outlook

Yahoo

iCloud

Fastmail

IMAP

Reason
Massive engineering overhead.
Add after traction.

B. Automation Rules
Auto‑delete

Auto‑block

Auto‑nuke

Auto‑archive

Rule suggestions

Reason
High risk.
Needs trust + data.

C. Full AI Janitor
Clustering

Domain rotation detection

Persistent offender detection

Advanced insights

Pattern modeling

Reason
Not needed for MVP dopamine loop.

D. Gamification (Advanced)
Boss fights

Zen mode

Rage mode

XP system

Badges

Titles

Reason
Add after core loop is validated.

E. Multi‑Inbox Control Center
Multiple accounts

Unified inbox

Cross‑provider rules

Reason
Too complex for MVP.

F. Deep Analytics
Inbox health score

Weekly reports

Trend analysis

Reason
Not essential for first release.

13.4 What’s Postponed (v1.5+)
These features are important, but not needed for MVP.

A. Boss Fights
High emotional payoff, but not required for core loop.

B. Zen/Rage Modes
Enhances experience, not required for functionality.

C. Advanced Insights
Requires more data + AI.

D. Multi‑Provider Support
Critical for growth, not for MVP.

E. Automation Rules
Must wait until trust is established.

13.5 What’s Essential (Must Ship)
These are non‑negotiable for MVP.

Swipe engine

Undo system

Gmail integration

Newsletter detection

Basic AI suggestions

Onboarding + trust

Mini victory screen

Progress bar

Basic insights

Domain nuke (with confirmation)

Logging + database

13.6 What’s Optional (Nice to Have)
If time allows:

Combo animations

Sound packs

Light gamification

Streaks

Sender avatars

Themed UI (garden/dojo)

Haptic variations

These improve emotional UX but are not required.

13.7 MVP Success Metrics
Product Metrics
Time to first swipe < 30 seconds

Emails cleared per session

Undo usage rate

Swipe completion rate

Session length

User Metrics
Day‑1 retention

Day‑7 retention

Gmail connection rate

Tutorial completion rate

Emotional Metrics
“Inbox feels lighter” feedback

User satisfaction

Repeat sessions

13.8 MVP Release Criteria
The MVP is ready when:

Swipe engine is flawless

Undo is 100% reliable

Gmail integration is stable

No irreversible actions exist

Onboarding builds trust

Users can clear 50 emails in < 2 minutes

Victory screen feels rewarding
